well as Hals's relationships with clients, pupils, and assistants, in order to gain a fuller grasp of the evolution of Hals's instantly recognizable style. A thoughtful study of the commercial and artistic concerns that shaped Hals's work, this book reflects on ideas of authorship, consumption, and subjectivity in early modern Europe. Combining smart historical analysis and a deep understanding of Dutch consumer culture with a strong sense of Hals as an artist, The Signature Style of Frans Hals offers a wholly new understanding of both the painter and his world. With discussions of two of Hals's most famous paintings, The Laughing Cavalier and The Gypsy Girl, this book is required reading for scholars of economic history, art historians, and anyone interested in gaining a deeper insight into life and times of this Dutch master.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPainting, Dutchy17th century. 4aART. 4aEarly Modern Period. 4aHistory. 7aART / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311070067108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060651508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066278840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048514595zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048514595423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048514595.jpg  a978-3-11-060651-5  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066278-8  Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2002d2015  a978-3-11-070067-1  AUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHAL